sub_title: Graduate student prev. @EEAS | Advanced MSc International Relations and Diplomacy | Leiden University | Journalist with work experience at DER SPIEGEL, ZDF Paris, Süddeutsche Zeitung and others
summary:
Katharina Horban is an alumna at Journalism School ifp and a fellow at Max Weber-Programm Bayern. She graduated with first class honours from LMU Munich in Political Science and Law. Currently, she pursues the Advanced MSc "International Relations and Diplomacy" (MIRD) at Leiden University. The programme takes place on the campus in The Hague, a hub of foreign embassies and international organisations.

Besides, Katharina works as a journalist. Her work got published in DER SPIEGEL, Süddeutsche Zeitung, FOCUS Magazin, ZDF heute, Tagesspiegel and Kieler Nachrichten so far.
